The paper deals with multiagent systems and control algorithms, which are typically studied in the cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) sub-category. The focus on resource allocation problems suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.GT (Game Theory) sub-category. The use of submodular functions and the analysis of a risk-reward tradeoff suggest that the paper may also belong to the cs.LG (Learning) sub-category. The study of distributed algorithms and the use of sensing and communication suggest that the paper may also belong to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category. Finally, the use of machine learning techniques and the study of performance guarantees suggest that the paper may also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category.
